The paper deals with distributed optimization algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community, and specifically focuses on the impact of adversarial nodes. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also involves graph theory and network analysis, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the impact of communication constraints and network topology, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
